chassisId.name: chassisId
chassisId.description: The unique identifier assigned to this station during manufacturing.

chassisType.name: chassisType
chassisType.description: The type of the LANplex chassis.

chassisRevision.name: chassisRevision
chassisRevision.description: The revision number of the LANplex chassis.

chassisName.name: chassisName
chassisName.description: The text string describing this chassis.

chassisNameAbbrev.name: chassisNameAbbrev
chassisNameAbbrev.description: The text string describing the generic name for this chassis.

chassisManufacturer.name: chassisManufacturer
chassisManufacturer.description: The text string describing the manufacturer of this chassis.

chassisSlotCount.name: chassisSlotCount
chassisSlotCount.description: The number of slots in the LANplex chassis.

chassisBuildTime.name: chassisBuildTime
chassisBuildTime.description: The build time of the LANplex system software.

chassisSoftwareRevision.name: chassisSoftwareRevision
chassisSoftwareRevision.description: The revision number of the LANplex system software. Each byte indicates the following: byte 0: major release number. byte 1: minor release number. byte 2: update number. byte 3: bits 7-6: release type. bits 5-0: supplemental idenrtifier.

chassisControlPanelColumns.name: chassisControlPanelColumns
chassisControlPanelColumns.description: The number of columns in the control panel display.

chassisControlPanelLines.name: chassisControlPanelLines
chassisControlPanelLines.description: The number of lines in the control panel display.

chassisControlPanelText.name: chassisControlPanelText
chassisControlPanelText.description: The currently displayed text in the control panel display.

chassisAction.name: chassisAction
chassisAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: reset: resets the LANplex system.

slotTable.name: slotTable
slotTable.description: A list of slot entries. A single instance of this object exists for each slot in the LANplex chassis.

slotEntry.name: slotEntry
slotEntry.description: A slot entry contains information common to a given slot within a LANplex system Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lpSlot table.

slotIndex.name: slotIndex
slotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LANplex chassis.

slotBoardType.name: slotBoardType
slotBoardType.description: The type of board residing in this slot.

slotBoardRevision.name: slotBoardRevision
slotBoardRevision.description: The revision number of the board in this slot.

slotBoardStatus.name: slotBoardStatus
slotBoardStatus.description: The status of the board in this slot.

slotBoardName.name: slotBoardName
slotBoardName.description: The text string describing this board type.

slotBoardNameAbbrev.name: slotBoardNameAbbrev
slotBoardNameAbbrev.description: The abbreviation used to describe this board type.

slotBoardAction.name: slotBoardAction
slotBoardAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: runDiagnostics: runs the board's offline diagnostics.

spmTable.name: spmTable
spmTable.description: A list of System Processor Module (SPM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is SPM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this SPM within the LANplex chassis. The entries may not have consecutive Slot Indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lpSlot table.

spmEntry.name: spmEntry
spmEntry.description: A SPM entry contains information common to a single System Processor Module (SPM) within a LANplex system.

spmSlotIndex.name: spmSlotIndex
spmSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LANplex chassis.

spmEthernetPortCount.name: spmEthernetPortCount
spmEthernetPortCount.description: The number of ethernet ports on this board.

spmBaseEthernetPortIndex.name: spmBaseEthernetPortIndex
spmBaseEthernetPortIndex.description: The system-wide index for the first ethernet port on this board.

feamTable.name: feamTable
feamTable.description: A list of FDDI Enterprise Access Module (FEAM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is FEAM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this FEAM within the LANplex chassis. The entries may not have consecutive Slot Indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lpSlot table.

feamEntry.name: feamEntry
feamEntry.description: A FEAM entry contains information common to a single FDDI Enterprise Access Module (FEAM) within a LANplex system.

feamSlotIndex.name: feamSlotIndex
feamSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LANplex chassis.

feamMACCount.name: feamMACCount
feamMACCount.description: The number of FDDI MAC's present on this board.

feamBaseMACIndex.name: feamBaseMACIndex
feamBaseMACIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI MAC on this board. Additional MAC's on this board will have consecutively increasing MAC indices following this index.

feamPortCount.name: feamPortCount
feamPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present on this board.

feamBasePortIndex.name: feamBasePortIndex
feamBasePortIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI port on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing Port indices following this index.

fcmTable.name: fcmTable
fcmTable.description: A list of FDDI Concentration Module (FCM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is FCM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this FCM within the LANplex chassis. The entries may not have consecutive Slot Indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lpSlot table.

fcmEntry.name: fcmEntry
fcmEntry.description: An FCM entry contains information common to a single FDDI Concentration Module (FCM) within a LANplex system.

fcmSlotIndex.name: fcmSlotIndex
fcmSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LANplex chassis.

fcmPortCount.name: fcmPortCount
fcmPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present on this board.

fcmBasePortIndex.name: fcmBasePortIndex
fcmBasePortIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI port on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing Port indices following this index.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: A list of port entries. A single instance of this object exists for each port (excluding ethernet ports) in the LANplex system. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available either via the fddiPort group or the enetPort group.

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: A Port entry contains information common to a particular port located on a particular board within the LANplex system.

portSlotIndex.name: portSlotIndex
portSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LANplex chassis.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: The index of the port on a particular slot.

portLabel.name: portLabel
portLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this port.

eemTable.name: eemTable
eemTable.description: A list of Ethernet Express Module (EEM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is EEM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this EEM within the LANplex chassis. The entries may not have consecutive Slot Indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available either via the slot group or the express group.

eemEntry.name: eemEntry
eemEntry.description: An EEM entry contains information common to a single Ethernet Express Module (EEM) within a LANplex system.

eemSlotIndex.name: eemSlotIndex
eemSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LANplex chassis.

eemFddiMACCount.name: eemFddiMACCount
eemFddiMACCount.description: The number of FDDI MAC's present on this board.

eemBaseFddiMACIndex.name: eemBaseFddiMACIndex
eemBaseFddiMACIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI MAC on this board. Additional FDDI MAC's on this board will have consecutively increasing MAC indices following this index.

eemEthernetPortCount.name: eemEthernetPortCount
eemEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet ports present on this board.

eemBaseEthernetPortIndex.name: eemBaseEthernetPortIndex
eemBaseEthernetPortIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first ethernet port on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing Port indices following this index.

eemAddressThreshold.name: eemAddressThreshold
eemAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of Ethernet Addresses known for this board. When this threshold is reached the event eemAddressThresholdEvent is generated.

eemFddiMACTable.name: eemFddiMACTable
eemFddiMACTable.description: A list of EEM FDDI MAC entries. The entries may not have consecutive slot indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the expressFddiPort group.

eemFddiMACEntry.name: eemFddiMACEntry
eemFddiMACEntry.description: An EEM FDDI MAC entry contains information common to an FDDI MAC located on an EEM within a LANplex system.

eemFddiSlotIndex.name: eemFddiSlotIndex
eemFddiSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this board.

eemFddiMACIndex.name: eemFddiMACIndex
eemFddiMACIndex.description: A unique value for each FDDI MAC on this board.

eemFddiMACForwardedCts.name: eemFddiMACForwardedCts
eemFddiMACForwardedCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames forwarded by a MAC from an ethernet port to the FDDI network.

eemFddiMACDroppedCts.name: eemFddiMACDroppedCts
eemFddiMACDroppedCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames that were dropped by a MAC due to local resource limitation or unknown destination MAC address.

eemEthernetPortTable.name: eemEthernetPortTable
eemEthernetPortTable.description: A list of EEM Ethernet Express Port entries. The slot indices may not be consecutive. The MAC indices will be consecutive. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the expressEthernetPort group.

eemEthernetPortEntry.name: eemEthernetPortEntry
eemEthernetPortEntry.description: An EEM Ethernet Express Port entry contains information common to an Ethenet Port located on an Ethernet Express Module (EEM) within a LANplex system.

eemEthernetPortSlotIndex.name: eemEthernetPortSlotIndex
eemEthernetPortSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the slot containing this port within the LANplex chassis.

eemEthernetPortIndex.name: eemEthernetPortIndex
eemEthernetPortIndex.description: The index of the port on a particular EEM board. This index ranges from 1 to eemEthernetPortCount.

eemEthernetPortLabel.name: eemEthernetPortLabel
eemEthernetPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this ethernet port.

eemEthernetPortForwardedCts.name: eemEthernetPortForwardedCts
eemEthernetPortForwardedCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames forwarded from this ethernet port on to the FDDI network.

eemEthernetPortDroppedCts.name: eemEthernetPortDroppedCts
eemEthernetPortDroppedCts.description: A counter indicating the numer of frames received on this port that were dropped due to the fact that the destination MAC address was determined to be on the same ethernet segment as the source MAC address. .

eemEthernetPortUTurnCts.name: eemEthernetPortUTurnCts
eemEthernetPortUTurnCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames received on this ethernet port and directed to another ethernet port.

eemEthernetPortState.name: eemEthernetPortState
eemEthernetPortState.description: The state of the Ethernet Express port.

eemEthernetPortAction.name: eemEthernetPortAction
eemEthernetPortAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from a port's address list. flushDynamicAddress: causes all the port's dynamic addresses to be flushed from a port's address list.

eemEthernetMACAddressTable.name: eemEthernetMACAddressTable
eemEthernetMACAddressTable.description: A list of EEM Ethernet Express Remote MAC Address entries. The slot indices may not be consecutive. The port indices will be consecutive. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lanplex MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the expressEthernetPort group.

eemEthernetMACAddressEntry.name: eemEthernetMACAddressEntry
eemEthernetMACAddressEntry.description: A collection of information describing a remote Ethernet MAC detected to be attached to an Ethernet Express port.

eemEthernetMACAddressSlotIndex.name: eemEthernetMACAddressSlotIndex
eemEthernetMACAddressSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the slot containing this EEM within the LANplex chassis.

eemEthernetMACAddressPortIndex.name: eemEthernetMACAddressPortIndex
eemEthernetMACAddressPortIndex.description: The port index of this address entry within the table. This index ranges from 1 to eemEthernetPortCount.

eemEthernetMACAddressIndex.name: eemEthernetMACAddressIndex
eemEthernetMACAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the table.

eemEthernetMACAddressType.name: eemEthernetMACAddressType
eemEthernetMACAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). Setting this object to invalid (2) will remove the corresponding address entry from the table.

eemEthernetMACAddressRemoteAddress.name: eemEthernetMACAddressRemoteAddress
eemEthernetMACAddressRemoteAddress.description: The remote MAC address detected on this Ethernet Express port.

eemEthernetMACAddressIsStatic.name: eemEthernetMACAddressIsStatic
eemEthernetMACAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or was dynamically learned on this port.

eemEthernetMACAddressStaticPort.name: eemEthernetMACAddressStaticPort
eemEthernetMACAddressStaticPort.description: If the object eemEthernetMACAddressIsStatic has value isStatic(1), this object indicates the port for which this MAC address was statically configured.

eemEthernetMACAddressAge.name: eemEthernetMACAddressAge
eemEthernetMACAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time elapsed since this MAC address was added to this port's address table.

lpSystemId.name: lpSystemId
lpSystemId.description: The unique identifier assigned to this system during manufacturing.

lpSystemType.name: lpSystemType
lpSystemType.description: The type of the LANplex system.

lpSystemName.name: lpSystemName
lpSystemName.description: The text string describing this system.

lpSystemManufacturer.name: lpSystemManufacturer
lpSystemManufacturer.description: The text string describing the manufacturer of this system.

lpSystemBackplaneRevision.name: lpSystemBackplaneRevision
lpSystemBackplaneRevision.description: The revision level of the system backplane. Bits 6 and 7 indicate the artwork revision. Bits 0 through 5 indicate the rework level.

lpSystemSlotCount.name: lpSystemSlotCount
lpSystemSlotCount.description: The number of slots in the system.

lpSystemMemorySize.name: lpSystemMemorySize
lpSystemMemorySize.description: The amount of memory (RAM), in bytes, present on the system processor board.

lpSystemFlashMemorySize.name: lpSystemFlashMemorySize
lpSystemFlashMemorySize.description: The amount of flash memory, in bytes, present on the system processor board.

lpSystemNvMemorySize.name: lpSystemNvMemorySize
lpSystemNvMemorySize.description: The amount of non-volatile memory, in bytes, present on the system processor board.

lpSystemSoftwareRevision.name: lpSystemSoftwareRevision
lpSystemSoftwareRevision.description: The revision number of the LANplex system software. Each byte indicates the following: byte 0: major release number. byte 1: minor release number. byte 2: update number. byte 3: bits 7-6: release type. bits 5-0: supplemental identifier.

lpSystemBuildTime.name: lpSystemBuildTime
lpSystemBuildTime.description: The build time of the system software.

lpSystemControlPanelHardwareRevision.name: lpSystemControlPanelHardwareRevision
lpSystemControlPanelHardwareRevision.description: An 8-bit value specifying the revision level of the control panel hardware.

lpSystemControlPanelSoftwareRevision.name: lpSystemControlPanelSoftwareRevision
lpSystemControlPanelSoftwareRevision.description: An 8-bit value specifying the revision level of the control panel software.

lpSystemControlPanelLines.name: lpSystemControlPanelLines
lpSystemControlPanelLines.description: The number of lines in the control panel display.

lpSystemControlPanelColumns.name: lpSystemControlPanelColumns
lpSystemControlPanelColumns.description: The number of columns in the control panel display.

lpSystemControlPanelText.name: lpSystemControlPanelText
lpSystemControlPanelText.description: The currently displayed text in the control panel display.

lpSystemFddiMacCount.name: lpSystemFddiMacCount
lpSystemFddiMacCount.description: The number of FDDI MAC's present in the system.

lpSystemFddiPortCount.name: lpSystemFddiPortCount
lpSystemFddiPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present in the system.

lpSystemEthernetPortCount.name: lpSystemEthernetPortCount
lpSystemEthernetPortCount.description: The number of ethernet ports present in the system.

lpSystemExpressFunctionCount.name: lpSystemExpressFunctionCount
lpSystemExpressFunctionCount.description: The number of Ethernet Express functions present in the system. Curently this value is equal to the number of Express boards present in the system.

lpSystemExpressFddiPortCount.name: lpSystemExpressFddiPortCount
lpSystemExpressFddiPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet Express FDDI ports present in the system.

lpSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.name: lpSystemExpressEthernetPortCount
lpSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet Express ethernet ports present in the system.

lpSystemPowerSupplyCount.name: lpSystemPowerSupplyCount
lpSystemPowerSupplyCount.description: The number of power supply units present in the system.

lpSystemAction.name: lpSystemAction
lpSystemAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: reset: resets the LANplex system.

lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.name: lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount
lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.description: The number of bridge functions present in the system. Curently this value is equal to the sum of the number of Express and Switching modules in the system.

lpSystemSmtProxyTimeoutBase.name: lpSystemSmtProxyTimeoutBase
lpSystemSmtProxyTimeoutBase.description: The initial timeout value, in seconds, before the SMT proxy attempts to backoff and retry. Since the SMT proxy will attempt three retries before determining that the proxied station is not answering, with the timeout doubling for each retry, the total time for a request to time out is equal to seven times the base timeout value.

lpSystemSmtProxyEvents.name: lpSystemSmtProxyEvents
lpSystemSmtProxyEvents.description: This object determines if the SMT proxy will generate traps for SMT events occuring at other stations. If enabled, the SMT proxy will generate traps for all SMT events, those that occur locally, and those that occur at other stations. If disabled, the SMT proxy will only generate traps for events which occur locally. The default value for this object is enabled(1).

lpSlotTable.name: lpSlotTable
lpSlotTable.description: A list of slot entries. A single instance of this object exists for each slot in the LANplex system.

lpSlotEntry.name: lpSlotEntry
lpSlotEntry.description: A slot entry contains information common to a given slot within a LANplex system.

lpSlotIndex.name: lpSlotIndex
lpSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the system.

lpSlotBoardType.name: lpSlotBoardType
lpSlotBoardType.description: The type of board residing in this slot.

lpSlotBoardRevision.name: lpSlotBoardRevision
lpSlotBoardRevision.description: The revision number of the board in this slot.

lpSlotBoardStatus.name: lpSlotBoardStatus
lpSlotBoardStatus.description: The status of the board in this slot.

lpSlotBoardName.name: lpSlotBoardName
lpSlotBoardName.description: The text string describing this board.

lpSlotBoardNameAbbrev.name: lpSlotBoardNameAbbrev
lpSlotBoardNameAbbrev.description: The abbreviation used to describe this board.

lpSlotFddiMacCount.name: lpSlotFddiMacCount
lpSlotFddiMacCount.description: The number of FDDI MAC's present in this slot.

lpSlotFddiMacBaseIndex.name: lpSlotFddiMacBaseIndex
lpSlotFddiMacBaseIndex.description: The index of the first FDDI MAC in this slot.

lpSlotFddiPortCount.name: lpSlotFddiPortCount
lpSlotFddiPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present in this slot.

lpSlotFddiPortBaseIndex.name: lpSlotFddiPortBaseIndex
lpSlotFddiPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first FDDI port in this slot.

lpSlotEthernetPortCount.name: lpSlotEthernetPortCount
lpSlotEthernetPortCount.description: The number of ethernet ports present in this slot.

lpSlotEthernetPortBaseIndex.name: lpSlotEthernetPortBaseIndex
lpSlotEthernetPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first ethernet port in this slot.

lpSlotExpressFunctionCount.name: lpSlotExpressFunctionCount
lpSlotExpressFunctionCount.description: The number of Express functions present in this slot.

lpSlotExpressFunctionBaseIndex.name: lpSlotExpressFunctionBaseIndex
lpSlotExpressFunctionBaseIndex.description: The index of the first Express function in this slot.

lpSlotExpressFddiPortCount.name: lpSlotExpressFddiPortCount
lpSlotExpressFddiPortCount.description: The number of Express FDDI ports present in this slot.

lpSlotExpressFddiPortBaseIndex.name: lpSlotExpressFddiPortBaseIndex
lpSlotExpressFddiPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first Express FDDI port in this slot.

lpSlotExpressEthernetPortCount.name: lpSlotExpressEthernetPortCount
lpSlotExpressEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Express ethernet ports present in this slot.

lpSlotExpressEthernetPortBaseIndex.name: lpSlotExpressEthernetPortBaseIndex
lpSlotExpressEthernetPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first Express ethernet port in this slot.

lpSlotBoardAction.name: lpSlotBoardAction
lpSlotBoardAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: runDiagnostics: runs the board's offline diagnostics.

lpSlotBridgeFunctionCount.name: lpSlotBridgeFunctionCount
lpSlotBridgeFunctionCount.description: The number of bridge functions present in this slot.

lpSlotBridgeFunctionBaseIndex.name: lpSlotBridgeFunctionBaseIndex
lpSlotBridgeFunctionBaseIndex.description: The index of the first bridge function in this slot.

lpFddiMacTable.name: lpFddiMacTable
lpFddiMacTable.description: A list of FDDI MAC entries. A single instance of this object exists for each FDDI MAC present in the system.

lpFddiMacEntry.name: lpFddiMacEntry
lpFddiMacEntry.description: An FDDI MAC entry contains information common to a particular FDDI MAC within the system.

lpFddiMacIndex.name: lpFddiMacIndex
lpFddiMacIndex.description: A unique value for each FDDI MAC in the system. The MAC identified by a particular value of this index is the same MAC as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

lpFddiMacSlotIndex.name: lpFddiMacSlotIndex
lpFddiMacSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this MAC.

lpFddiMacLocalIndex.name: lpFddiMacLocalIndex
lpFddiMacLocalIndex.description: The index of this MAC relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpFddiMacByteReceiveRate.name: lpFddiMacByteReceiveRate
lpFddiMacByteReceiveRate.description: The average number of bytes received per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lpFddiMacPeakByteReceiveRate.name: lpFddiMacPeakByteReceiveRate
lpFddiMacPeakByteReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lpFddiMacByteReceiveRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lpFddiMacFrameReceiveRate.name: lpFddiMacFrameReceiveRate
lpFddiMacFrameReceiveRate.description: The average number of frames received per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lpFddiMacPeakFrameReceiveRate.name: lpFddiMacPeakFrameReceiveRate
lpFddiMacPeakFrameReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lpFddiMacFrameReceiveRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lpFddiMacByteTransmitRate.name: lpFddiMacByteTransmitRate
lpFddiMacByteTransmitRate.description: The average number of bytes transmitted per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lpFddiMacPeakByteTransmitRate.name: lpFddiMacPeakByteTransmitRate
lpFddiMacPeakByteTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lpFddiMacByteTransmitRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lpFddiMacFrameTransmitRate.name: lpFddiMacFrameTransmitRate
lpFddiMacFrameTransmitRate.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lpFddiMacPeakFrameTransmitRate.name: lpFddiMacPeakFrameTransmitRate
lpFddiMacPeakFrameTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lpFddiMacFrameTransmitRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lpFddiMacReceiveMulticastThreshold.name: lpFddiMacReceiveMulticastThreshold
lpFddiMacReceiveMulticastThreshold.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is one second. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

lpFddiMacBeaconHistory.name: lpFddiMacBeaconHistory
lpFddiMacBeaconHistory.description: This object gives a history of the most recent beacon information received on this MAC. It can contain up to a maximum of eight records. Each record is of the form: source MAC: 6 bytes beacon data length: 2 bytes. beacon data: 0-16 bytes.

lpEthernetPortTable.name: lpEthernetPortTable
lpEthernetPortTable.description: A list of ethernet port entries. A single instance of this object exists for each ethernet port present in the system.

lpEthernetPortEntry.name: lpEthernetPortEntry
lpEthernetPortEntry.description: An ethernet port entry contains information common to a particular ethernet port within the system.

lpEthernetPortIndex.name: lpEthernetPortIndex
lpEthernetPortIndex.description: A unique value for each ethernet port in the system. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

lpEthernetPortSlotIndex.name: lpEthernetPortSlotIndex
lpEthernetPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lpEthernetPortLocalIndex.name: lpEthernetPortLocalIndex
lpEthernetPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpEthernetPortLabel.name: lpEthernetPortLabel
lpEthernetPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this port.

lpEthernetPortChipsetType.name: lpEthernetPortChipsetType
lpEthernetPortChipsetType.description: The type of chipset used to implement this port.

lpEthernetPortLinkStatus.name: lpEthernetPortLinkStatus
lpEthernetPortLinkStatus.description: The current value of the link status for this port.

lpEthernetPortByteReceiveRate.name: lpEthernetPortByteReceiveRate
lpEthernetPortByteReceiveRate.description: The average number of bytes received per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lpEthernetPortPeakByteReceiveRate.name: lpEthernetPortPeakByteReceiveRate
lpEthernetPortPeakByteReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lpEthernetPortByteReceiveRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lpEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate.name: lpEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate
lpEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate.description: The average number of frames received per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lpEthernetPortPeakFrameReceiveRate.name: lpEthernetPortPeakFrameReceiveRate
lpEthernetPortPeakFrameReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lpEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lpEthernetPortByteTransmitRate.name: lpEthernetPortByteTransmitRate
lpEthernetPortByteTransmitRate.description: The average number of bytes transmitted per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lpEthernetPortPeakByteTransmitRate.name: lpEthernetPortPeakByteTransmitRate
lpEthernetPortPeakByteTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lpEthernetPortByteTransmitRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lpEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate.name: lpEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate
lpEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lpEthernetPortPeakFrameTransmitRate.name: lpEthernetPortPeakFrameTransmitRate
lpEthernetPortPeakFrameTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lpEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lpEthernetPortReceiveMulticastThreshold.name: lpEthernetPortReceiveMulticastThreshold
lpEthernetPortReceiveMulticastThreshold.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is four seconds. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

lpEthernetPortType.name: lpEthernetPortType
lpEthernetPortType.description: Specific description of this port's type.

lpFddiPortTable.name: lpFddiPortTable
lpFddiPortTable.description: A list of FDDI port entries. A single instance of this object exists for each FDDI port in the system.

lpFddiPortEntry.name: lpFddiPortEntry
lpFddiPortEntry.description: A Port entry contains information common to a particular FDDI port in the system.

lpFddiPortIndex.name: lpFddiPortIndex
lpFddiPortIndex.description: A unique value for each FDDI port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemFddiPortCount.

lpFddiPortSlotIndex.name: lpFddiPortSlotIndex
lpFddiPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lpFddiPortLocalIndex.name: lpFddiPortLocalIndex
lpFddiPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpFddiPortLabel.name: lpFddiPortLabel
lpFddiPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this port.

lpExpressTable.name: lpExpressTable
lpExpressTable.description: A list of Express function entries.

lpExpressEntry.name: lpExpressEntry
lpExpressEntry.description: An Express entry contains information common to a particular Express function in a given system.

lpExpressIndex.name: lpExpressIndex
lpExpressIndex.description: A unique value for each Express function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemExpressFunctionCount.

lpExpressSlotIndex.name: lpExpressSlotIndex
lpExpressSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this function.

lpExpressLocalIndex.name: lpExpressLocalIndex
lpExpressLocalIndex.description: The index of this function relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpExpressAddressThreshold.name: lpExpressAddressThreshold
lpExpressAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of Ethernet Addresses known for this board. When this threshold is reached, the event lpEemAddressThresholdEvent is generated.

lpExpressFddiPortTable.name: lpExpressFddiPortTable
lpExpressFddiPortTable.description: A list of Express FDDI port entries.

lpExpressFddiPortEntry.name: lpExpressFddiPortEntry
lpExpressFddiPortEntry.description: A Port entry contains information for a particular Express FDDI port in a given system.

lpExpressFddiPortIndex.name: lpExpressFddiPortIndex
lpExpressFddiPortIndex.description: A unique value for each Express port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemExpressFddiPortCount.

lpExpressFddiPortSlotIndex.name: lpExpressFddiPortSlotIndex
lpExpressFddiPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lpExpressFddiPortLocalIndex.name: lpExpressFddiPortLocalIndex
lpExpressFddiPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpExpressFddiPortForwardedCts.name: lpExpressFddiPortForwardedCts
lpExpressFddiPortForwardedCts.description: The number of frames forwarded by this MAC from an ethernet port to the FDDI network.

lpExpressFddiPortDroppedCts.name: lpExpressFddiPortDroppedCts
lpExpressFddiPortDroppedCts.description: The number of frames received by this MAC that were not forwarded.

lpExpressEthernetPortTable.name: lpExpressEthernetPortTable
lpExpressEthernetPortTable.description: A list of Express ethernet port entries.

lpExpressEthernetPortEntry.name: lpExpressEthernetPortEntry
lpExpressEthernetPortEntry.description: An Expres ethernet port entry contains information common to a particular Express ethernet port located in the system.

lpExpressEthernetPortIndex.name: lpExpressEthernetPortIndex
lpExpressEthernetPortIndex.description: A unique value for each Express ethernet port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.

lpExpressEthernetPortSlotIndex.name: lpExpressEthernetPortSlotIndex
lpExpressEthernetPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lpExpressEthernetPortLocalIndex.name: lpExpressEthernetPortLocalIndex
lpExpressEthernetPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpExpressEthernetPortForwardedCts.name: lpExpressEthernetPortForwardedCts
lpExpressEthernetPortForwardedCts.description: The number of frames forwarded from this ethernet port to the FDDI network.

lpExpressEthernetPortDroppedCts.name: lpExpressEthernetPortDroppedCts
lpExpressEthernetPortDroppedCts.description: The number of frames received by this ethernet port that were not forwarded or u-turned.

lpExpressEthernetPortUTurnCts.name: lpExpressEthernetPortUTurnCts
lpExpressEthernetPortUTurnCts.description: The number of frames received by this ethernet port that were directed to another ethernet port.

lpExpressEthernetPortAction.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAction
lpExpressEthernetPortAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from a port's address list. flushDynamicAddress: causes all the port's dynamic addresses to be flushed from a port's address list.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressTable.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressTable
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressTable.description: A list of Express Remote MAC Address entries.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressEntry.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressEntry
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressEntry.description: An entry contains information describing a remote Ethernet MAC detected to be attached to an Express port.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressPortIndex.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressPortIndex
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressPortIndex.description: A unique value for each Express ethernet port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIndex.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIndex
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the address table.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressSlotIndex.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressSlotIndex
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressType.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressType
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). Setting this object to invalid (2) will remove the corresponding address entry from the table.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressRemoteAddres.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressRemoteAddress
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressRemoteAddres.description: The remote MAC address detected on this port.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or was dynamically learned on this port.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressStaticPort.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressStaticPort
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressStaticPort.description: If the object lpExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic has value isStatic(1), this object indicates the port for which this MAC address was statically configured.

lpExpressEthernetPortAddressAge.name: lpExpressEthernetPortAddressAge
lpExpressEthernetPortAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time, in seconds, elapsed since this MAC address was added to this port's address table.

lpPowerSupplyTable.name: lpPowerSupplyTable
lpPowerSupplyTable.description: A list of power supply entries.

lpPowerSupplyEntry.name: lpPowerSupplyEntry
lpPowerSupplyEntry.description: A power supply entry contains information common for a particular power supply unit in the system.

lpPowerSupplyIndex.name: lpPowerSupplyIndex
lpPowerSupplyIndex.description: A unique value for each power supply in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemPowerSupplyCount.

lpPowerSupplyLocation.name: lpPowerSupplyLocation
lpPowerSupplyLocation.description: The physical slot in which this power supply unit resides in the system.

lpPowerSupplyStatus.name: lpPowerSupplyStatus
lpPowerSupplyStatus.description: The status of the power supply. A value of 0 indicates a working unit. A non-zero value represents a bit mask of the possible failure types. Each set bit indicates the following failure type: bit0: systemAcFailure bit1: systemPlus5Failure bit2: systemPlus12Failure bit3: systemOverTemperatureFailure.

lpPowerSupplyFailureType.name: lpPowerSupplyFailureType
lpPowerSupplyFailureType.description: This object is sent in the varlist when the lpPowerSupplyFailureEvent trap is generated. It indicates the particular failure type that caused this trap to be generated.

lpPowerSupplyLastFailure.name: lpPowerSupplyLastFailure
lpPowerSupplyLastFailure.description: This object represents the most recent power supply failure type. If no failure has occured, the value of this object is none. This object is included in the varlist when the lpPowerSupplyFailureEvent trap is generated. It indicates the failure type that caused the trap to be generated.

lpBridgeTable.name: lpBridgeTable
lpBridgeTable.description: A list of bridge function entries.

lpBridgeEntry.name: lpBridgeEntry
lpBridgeEntry.description: A bridge entry contains information common to a particular bridge function in a given system.

lpBridgeIndex.name: lpBridgeIndex
lpBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lpBridgeBaseSlotIndex.name: lpBridgeBaseSlotIndex
lpBridgeBaseSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the lowest numbered slot which contains a physical port that this bridge function controls.

lpBridgePortCount.name: lpBridgePortCount
lpBridgePortCount.description: The number of ports that this bridge function controls.

lpBridgeAddressTableSize.name: lpBridgeAddressTableSize
lpBridgeAddressTableSize.description: The size of the address table for this bridge function.

lpBridgeAddressThreshold.name: lpBridgeAddressThreshold
lpBridgeAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of addresses known for this board. When this threshold is reached, the event lpBridgeAddressThresholdEvent is generated. The range of valid values for setting this object is between 1 and the value reported by lpBridgeAddressTableSize + 1 (Note that this range applies to values issued in set requests. The current value may be outside this range, for example if the value of lpBridgeMode is changed). Setting this object to one greater than the address table size disables the generation of lpBridgeAddressThresholdEvents since the limit will never be reached.

lpBridgeMode.name: lpBridgeMode
lpBridgeMode.description: The operational mode of this bridge function. Note that bridges which report notSupported(3) will not support sets of this object, and that the value notSupported(3) is not a valid value for a set operation.

lpBridgeLocalIndex.name: lpBridgeLocalIndex
lpBridgeLocalIndex.description: The index of this bridge function relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lpBridgePortTable.name: lpBridgePortTable
lpBridgePortTable.description: A list of bridge port entries.

lpBridgePortEntry.name: lpBridgePortEntry
lpBridgePortEntry.description: A Port entry contains information for a particular bridge port in a given system.

lpBridgePortBridgeIndex.name: lpBridgePortBridgeIndex
lpBridgePortBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lpBridgePortIndex.name: lpBridgePortIndex
lpBridgePortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references.

lpBridgePortSlotIndex.name: lpBridgePortSlotIndex
lpBridgePortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lpBridgePortLocalIndex.name: lpBridgePortLocalIndex
lpBridgePortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present and its port type. For example FDDI ports in a slot are identified with local indices from 1 to the number of FDDI ports in that slot, and the Ethernet ports in the same slot are identified with local indices from 1 to the number of Ethernet ports in that slot.

lpBridgePortIpFragmentationEnabled.name: lpBridgePortIpFragmentationEnabled
lpBridgePortIpFragmentationEnabled.description: A flag indicating whether or not IP fragmentation is enabled on this bridge port. Note that bridges which report notSupported(3) will not support sets of this object, and that the value notSupported(3) is not a valid value for a set operation.

lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit.name: lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit
lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is one second. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

lpBridgePortAddressAction.name: lpBridgePortAddressAction
lpBridgePortAddressAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from the port's address list. flushDynamicAddress: causes all dynamic addresses to be flushed from the port's address list.

lpBridgePortTotalForwardedCts.name: lpBridgePortTotalForwardedCts
lpBridgePortTotalForwardedCts.description: The total number of frames forwarded from this port to all other ports of this bridge. Note that the total forwarded count is NOT equal to the receive count minus the discard count, as a single received multicast/broadcast frame can be forwarded to multiple bridge ports. Also frames which are 'flooded' because of unknown destination addresses account for multiple forwarding as well. The total forwarding count is the instantaneous sumation of the 'forwarded to' counts to all other ports of the bridge.

lpBridgePortManagementFramesReceived.name: lpBridgePortManagementFramesReceived
lpBridgePortManagementFramesReceived.description: The number of bridge management frames received by this port.

lpBridgePortTotalDiscards.name: lpBridgePortTotalDiscards
lpBridgePortTotalDiscards.description: The total number of frames discarded by this port.

lpBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards.name: lpBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards
lpBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the the receiving bridge port was not in the 'forwarding' state.

lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.name: lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceededs
lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.description: The number of multicast/broadcast frames discarded by this port because the lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit was exceeded.

lpBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards.name: lpBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards
lpBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because they contained source addresses which were statically configured on another bridge port. A statically configured address (station), which is not allowed to move, appears to have moved.

lpBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards.name: lpBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards
lpBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the destination address was unknown. Note that this counter is only valid for FDDI ports, and only when the bridge is an EEM, or an ESM operating in express mode.

lpBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards.name: lpBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards
lpBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because they contained either invalid (group) source addresses or source addresses belonging to this bridge (indicative of network loops).

lpBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards.name: lpBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards
lpBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because of internal bridge system errors (e.g., hardware and software address table discrepencies).

lpBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards.name: lpBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards
lpBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the destination address is known on the same network segment as the source address, i.e., the frame does not need to be bridged.

lpBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards.name: lpBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards
lpBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the the transmitting bridge port was not in the 'forwarding' state.

lpBridgePortTotalFiltered.name: lpBridgePortTotalFiltered
lpBridgePortTotalFiltered.description: The total number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined filters.

lpBridgePortReceiveUnicastFiltered.name: lpBridgePortReceiveUnicastFiltered
lpBridgePortReceiveUnicastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined receive path filters.

lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastFiltered.name: lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastFiltered
lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined receive multicast path filters.

lpBridgePortTransmitUnicastFiltered.name: lpBridgePortTransmitUnicastFiltered
lpBridgePortTransmitUnicastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined transmit path filters.

lpBridgePortTransmitMulticastFiltered.name: lpBridgePortTransmitMulticastFiltered
lpBridgePortTransmitMulticastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined transmit multicast path filters.

lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.name: lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceededCount
lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.description: The number of times the lpBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit was exceeded.

lpBridgePortForwardedToTable.name: lpBridgePortForwardedToTable
lpBridgePortForwardedToTable.description: A list of port forwarding count information.

lpBridgePortForwardedToEntry.name: lpBridgePortForwardedToEntry
lpBridgePortForwardedToEntry.description: A bridge port forwarded-to entry contains information on the count of frames forwarded from the receiving port indicated by the corresponding lpBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex, to the destination port indicated by the corresponding lpBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex. Note that no entries exist which are indexed with the same values for both the lpBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex and the lpBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex objects.

lpBridgePortForwardedToBridgeIndex.name: lpBridgePortForwardedToBridgeIndex
lpBridgePortForwardedToBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lpBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex.name: lpBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex
lpBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the receiving port which is forwarding frames.

lpBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex.name: lpBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex
lpBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the destination port to which frames are being forwarded.

lpBridgePortForwardedToCount.name: lpBridgePortForwardedToCount
lpBridgePortForwardedToCount.description: The count of frames forwarded from the receiving port to the destination port.

lpBridgePortFilteredToTable.name: lpBridgePortFilteredToTable
lpBridgePortFilteredToTable.description: A list of port filtering count information.

lpBridgePortFilteredToEntry.name: lpBridgePortFilteredToEntry
lpBridgePortFilteredToEntry.description: A bridge port filtered-to entry contains information on the count of frames filtered from the receiving port indicated by the corresponding lpBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex, to the destination port indicated by the corresponding lpBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex. Note that no entries exist which are indexed with the same values for both the lpBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex and the lpBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex objects.

lpBridgePortFilteredToBridgeIndex.name: lpBridgePortFilteredToBridgeIndex
lpBridgePortFilteredToBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lpBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex.name: lpBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex
lpBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the receiving port which is filtering frames.

lpBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex.name: lpBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex
lpBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the destination port to which frames are being filtered.

lpBridgePortFilteredToCount.name: lpBridgePortFilteredToCount
lpBridgePortFilteredToCount.description: The count of frames filtered from the receiving port to the destination port.

lpBridgePortAddressTable.name: lpBridgePortAddressTable
lpBridgePortAddressTable.description: A list of bridge port address entries.

lpBridgePortAddressEntry.name: lpBridgePortAddressEntry
lpBridgePortAddressEntry.description: An bridge port address entry contains information about particular bridge port address in a given system.

lpBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex.name: lpBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex
lpBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lpBridgePortAddressPortIndex.name: lpBridgePortAddressPortIndex
lpBridgePortAddressPortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lpBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references.

lpBridgePortAddressIndex.name: lpBridgePortAddressIndex
lpBridgePortAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the bridge address table.

lpBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress.name: lpBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress
lpBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress.description: The remote MAC address detected on the port corresponding to this entry. Setting this object attempts to create a new entry in the table. Since the value of lpBridgePortAddressIndex is determined automatically internal to the bridge, a set is only successful if the index value specified for lpBridgePortAddressIndex is zero. A get-next using the values of lpBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex and lpBridgePortAddressPortIndex can be used to determine the address index assigned to the newly added address entry.

lpBridgePortAddressType.name: lpBridgePortAddressType
lpBridgePortAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). Setting this object to invalid (2) will remove the corresponding address entry from the table.

lpBridgePortAddressIsStatic.name: lpBridgePortAddressIsStatic
lpBridgePortAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or was dynamically learned.

lpBridgePortAddressStaticPort.name: lpBridgePortAddressStaticPort
lpBridgePortAddressStaticPort.description: If the object lpBridgePortAddressIsStatic has value isStatic(1), this object indicates the local port index (as reported by lpBridgePortLocalIndex) for which this MAC address was statically configured. If the object lpBridgePortAddressIsStatic has the value isDynamic(2), the value of this object is 0.

lpBridgePortAddressAge.name: lpBridgePortAddressAge
lpBridgePortAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time, in seconds, elapsed since a packet containing this address as a source was last seen on the port corresponding to this entry.

lpTrapEnterpriseTable.name: lpTrapEnterpriseTable
lpTrapEnterpriseTable.description: This table contains a listing of enterprises under which various traps are defined. In all cases except for the MIB-II generic traps, the enterprise under which a trap is defined is the same as that appearing in the ENTERPRISE portion of the trap. Associated with each trap enterprise is a trap enterprise index.

lpTrapEnterpriseTableEntry.name: lpTrapEnterpriseTableEntry
lpTrapEnterpriseTableEntry.description: Information relating a specific trap enterprise OID with a trap enterprise index.

lpTrapEnterpriseIndex.name: lpTrapEnterpriseIndex
lpTrapEnterpriseIndex.description: A unique index corresponding to a particular enterprise OID under which traps are defined. This value of this object corresponding to a particular enterprise OID will remain constant accross system resets.

lpTrapEnterpriseOID.name: lpTrapEnterpriseOID
lpTrapEnterpriseOID.description: An enterpise OID under which traps are defined.

lpTrapDestTable.name: lpTrapDestTable
lpTrapDestTable.description: This table contains information specifying which traps will be transmitted by the LANplex to a given destination address. The table is indexed by the destination address, the index of the enterprise which generates the trap, and the trap number. Each entry in the table with a status of valid identifies a trap which, when generated, will be transmitted to the corresponding destination address listed in that entry.

lpTrapDestTableEntry.name: lpTrapDestTableEntry
lpTrapDestTableEntry.description: Information relating a trap with a destination address to which the trap will be sent when it is generated.

lpTrapDestAddr.name: lpTrapDestAddr
lpTrapDestAddr.description: The network address to which the trap identified by this entry is to be transmitted.

lpTrapDestEnterpriseIndex.name: lpTrapDestEnterpriseIndex
lpTrapDestEnterpriseIndex.description: The enterprise index of the enterprise identified in this entry. The value of this object is the same as the lpTrapEnterpriseIndex value for a given enterprise.

lpTrapNumber.name: lpTrapNumber
lpTrapNumber.description: The number of the trap within the corresponding enterprise for this entry.

lpTrapEntryStatus.name: lpTrapEntryStatus
lpTrapEntryStatus.description: The status of the trap destination table entry. Setting this object to valid has the effect of attempting to add the row corresponding to the instance specified. If the instance already exists, the set is successful (with no new entry added). If the instance specified is invalid, the set fails, otherwise the set succeeds and results in a new entry being added to the table. Setting this object to invalid has the effect of removing the corresponding entry from the table.

lpSlotInsertEvent.name: lpSlotInsertEvent
lpSlotInsertEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a board is inserted into a particular slot in the chassis.

lpSlotExtractEvent.name: lpSlotExtractEvent
lpSlotExtractEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a board is extracted from a particular slot in the chassis.

lpBridgeAddressThresholdEvent.name: lpBridgeAddressThresholdEvent
lpBridgeAddressThresholdEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the number of addresses stored in the bridge reaches lpBridgeAddressThreshold.

lpSystemOverTemperatureEvent.name: lpSystemOverTemperatureEvent
lpSystemOverTemperatureEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the system temperature exceeds a certain threshold.

lpSlotOverTemperatureEvent.name: lpSlotOverTemperatureEvent
lpSlotOverTemperatureEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the temperature of a board in a particular slot exceeds a certain threshold.

lpPowerSupplyFailureEvent.name: lpPowerSupplyFailureEvent
lpPowerSupplyFailureEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a power supply unit fails in the system.
